cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.RO 

The paper presents a novel theoretical framework for black-box optimization, which is primarily important for many compute-intensive applications, including reinforcement learning (RL), robot control, etc. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), systems and control (cs.SY), and robotics (cs.RO).
